Claims CLAIMS  Therefore, the following is claimed: 1. A system for relaying and caching authentication credentials, comprising: a computing device comprising a processor and a memory; machine -readable instructions stored in the memory that, when executed by the processor, cause the computing device to at least: receive a single sign-on (SSO) token, the SSO token representing a user account authenticated with an identity manager; send an authentication request to a service that is federated with the identity manager in response to receipt of the SSO token, the authentication request comprising the SSO token; receive an access token in response to the authentication request, the access token providing access to the service for the user account authenticated with the identity manager for a predefined period of time; and cache the access token and a link between the access token and the SSO token. 2. The system of claim 1, wherein the authentication request is a first authentication request, the access token is a first access token, the predefined period of time is a first predefined of time, and the machine-readable instructions stored in the memory, when executed by the processor, further cause the computing device to further at least: receive a refresh token in response to the authentication request; determine that the predefined period of time that the access token is authorized to provide access to the service for the user account has expired; send a second authentication request to the service that is federated with the identity manager, the second authentication request comprising the refresh token; 

 receive a second access token in response to the second authentication request, the second access token providing access to the service for the user account authenticated with the identity manager for a second predefined period of time; and cache the second access token and a second link between the second access token and the SSO token. 3. The system of claim 1, wherein the machine-readable instructions stored in the memory, when executed by the processor, further cause the computing device to further at least: receive a request for the access token from an application, the request for the access token comprising the SSO token; and provide the access token linked to the SSO token to the application. 4. The system of claim 1, wherein the machine-readable instructions that cause the computing device to send the authentication request to the service that is federated with the identity manager further cause the computing device to navigate a user-consent workflow provided by the service. 5. The system of claim 1, wherein the machine readable instructions, when executed by the processor, further cause the computing device to at least: receive a request for a list of services associated with the user account represented by the SSO token; and provide a list of services for which the SSO token is permitted access. 6. The system of claim 1, wherein the authentication request is sent in compliance with a version of the OAUTH protocol. 7. The system of claim 1, wherein the SSO token is a JSON web token. 8. A method of relaying and caching authentication credentials, comprising: receiving a single sign-on (SSO) token, the SSO token representing a user account authenticated with an identity manager; sending an authentication request to a service that is federated with the identity manager in response to receipt of the SSO token, the authentication request comprising the SSO token; receiving an access token in response to the authentication request, the access token providing a